					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1606990#post-2463436</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1606990/scp-2227#post-2463436</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 26 Feb 2016 00:54:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MrRonin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1833724</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>SCP-2227-A is trapped within the subway systems, just like the rest of the hobos. He's using people to his advantage, and he is well aware of this. I won't say exactly <em>why</em> he's doing it, but the people in the pictures he points out to (as told by George) are part of the reason.</p> <p>SCP-2227-A isn't a total bad guy either. George was the first person to not see the shadow man as a brooding eldritch monster, but rather as someone who also happens to be stuck. Assuming SCP-2227-A has full control over who becomes a ghost hobo, he has perhaps even recruited people for help, rather than labor.</p> <p>And maybe, just maybe, SCP-2227-A has gotten a change of heart.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
