					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1606990#post-2460246</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1606990/scp-2227#post-2460246</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 20 Feb 2016 12:16:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Petrograd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>455145</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>On the minus side, your method for presenting amended procedures was not super effective without a re-read, and similarly some parts of the description weren't entirely clear.</p> <p>(Also, on a philosophical level, the huge number of ghosts in the room suggests explaining New York homelessness through an SCP, which leans towards that taking-inappropriate-credit-for-real-tragedy pitfall for me. This isn't a huge complaint from me, since it's a damn good story, just enough to be worth mentioning.)</p> <p>On the plus side, the story as told through the event and interviews was deeply engrossing, appropriately nonsensical, and still mysterious enough to survive the explaining. Well done.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
